 The update, KB4524244, was released on February 11, as part of Microsoft’s normally scheduled Patch Tuesday release  The update, KB4524244, was released on February 11, as part of Microsoft’s normally scheduled Patch Tuesday release, but the company revoked it late on Friday. “This standalone security update has been removed due to an issue affecting a subset of devices,” Microsoft said in an advisory. “It will not be re-offered from Windows Update, Windows Server Update Services (WSUS) or Microsoft Update Catalogue.”  To enable commenting and other interactive features, please switch to the more advanced .